Hey all! New here, got some odd behaviour with web hooks, who is the best person to talk to?

What I am experiencing is a bit odd (way around it but still odd).

I create a company, enter just the name, click create - web hook comes through with company.creation, great works as expected.

I create a company, enter domain, let it fill out all the info, click create, web hook comes through like so:

[0] company.propertyChange
[1] company.propertyChange
[2] company.propertyChange
[3] company.creation
[4] company.propertyChange

Now you might say this is fine, whats the issue?

Yes I check the IDs in another system when looking up so I will know if the HubSpot ID sent over doesn’t yet exist but why does HubSpot send them in this order?

Surely company.creation should always be the first in the stack (before related company.propertyChange events) and on company.creation do we need to trigger company.propertyChange events?

Has anyone else noticed this behaviour?
we have a sync from hightouch into Zendesk
and native from Zendesk to HubSpot
but we only want to pull users to HubSpot
where a specific field has a known value
is this possible?
you'll save me 2 weeks of work if I know the answer to this one in 30 minutes :joy::sweat_smile:
So you would like to send them from hightouch directly to HubSpot?
hightouch goes to zendesk already
from which we want it to go to HubSpot
but lets say there are 10 million actual users in zendesk
and 100 million accounts
we only want those 10 million actual users
which have a value in the seller ID field
so all you need is a sync between HS and zendesk based on that seller ID field?
yes
just need to know if it's possible to stop it from syncing ones without a value in that field
otherwise my DB is filled with ... stuff
refuse, lets call it
do you use the native Zendesk to HubSpot integration for anything else than syncing this user data?
no
do you have operations hub pro?
yes
then it might be possible
do you happen to know how it might be done?
